         The problem with making DOTs a DD with a long recast is resists.  If you have a DOT now resisted you cast it again until it lands (waiting only a few seconds between) but if it has a huge recast time you have to wait 1 minute or maybe more!  On a highly resistant mob that means you're gonna spend a lot of time waiting for gems to refresh.  It also means that memming a new spell takes forever for the gem to light up.  Switching gems constantly (as I understand a necro has to do to be truly useful) is a real problem because a dot will take forever and a day to light up.</P><P>Crilk<BR>56 master of the order of Fist and Tail/Lost Circle<BR>Druzzil Ro</P><P>Chakru<BR>35 student of dark heraldry</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
