        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This is in response the the person who thought folks could exploit DoT stacking by zoning out and back in to smack some more dots on a given critter.</P><P>1)  As soon as you zone and are off the hate list, all mobs regen at an amazing rate so that would take a big dent out of your efficiency, especially when you consider a minimum of 30 secs to zone out and back in.</P><P>2) If DoT stacking were based on the structure I mention earlier, i.e, Spell_Ident+Char+PID, then when you zoned back in, the mob would still have that effect active and when you cast it again, it would overwrite it, not stack.</P><P>For those who didn't read my previous post, Spell_Ident is the numerical identifier currently in game for every spell (see Lucy) and Char_PID is the unique player identifier.  This latter may well be a hashed version for the player's Station_ID since it is the same for all characters on a given account.</P><P>Someone buy me a ticket to San Diego and I'll have this all fixed up in a week ;-P  Before the flames begin...that was a lil' joke.  I'm sure my suggestion is fraught with problems but the basic premise is sound.</P><P>ta,<BR>=SV=</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
