         I see it another way I mean vereant should inpliment dot stacking but it wont be as much work as they let on I mean not all npc's will have to have the buff slots increased. I mean there is no real point to increase  everday mobs buff slots. 15 for most xp situations is wonderful andmost necros seem to  agree that any creature under 100 000hp is generaly dead before our dots do much damage.</P><P>SO realy all they have to do is make all the creatures with x amount of hit points have say 60 buff slots work out what dots should stack etc and fix the problem with bard songs. I mean there will be major issues there mainly because most bard songs have debuffing conponets.<BR>but its very doable.</P><P>And as for the posible exploits such as fd to clear agro most classes have abilities like that wizards get a spell to lower agro so do rangers and a few other classes . monks reglarly fd to remove agro etc so that cant be the exploit there thinkin of. and as for dotting some one and zoneing thats been an exploit for a while its incredibly easy to power level some one that way.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
